Chief Executive Officer Job (CEO Job) (Joint-Venture), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Chief Executive Officer Job (CEO Job) (Joint-Venture), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of an expanding joint-venture E-commerce company within the financial services industry, in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a candidate for the job of Chief Executive Officer (CEO), to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will be required to develop models, leverage social media platforms to drive customer engagement and implement ways to achieve profit growth for this start-up e-commerce firm. The successful applicant must be a great communicator and leader who drives enthusiasm, momentum and collaboration around a shared vision for sustainable businesses. The winning candidate will report directly to the respective partners of the joint-ventures. Key job responsibilities include: Plans, directs, organizes and schedules the strategies and activities of the firm.Oversee the company’s’ online sales and brand presence.Conveying a consistent brand image that attracts customers by enticing sales on the web.Analyse the business and operations of the start-up and online marketing in Indonesia.Optimize the e-commerce platform by establishing best proven practices, processes, measurement and forecasting systems.Plan and execute the strategic move of the start-up and liaise with the partners.Lead and execute a methodology that accurately predicts sales, orders, customer acquisition and costs for all programs.Support company and department goals and achieve business unit KPI's.Liaise with peers in Finance, Customer Support, IT, and Creative to deliver an unrivalled customer experience for all sales channels.Provide backend analysis and recommendations after testing to continuously improve the customer experience and grow sales and contribution.Analyse and provide reporting on program KPI's – identifying opportunities for growth and improving efficiency.Execute trend analysis, monitoring and competitive benchmarking. Job Requirements  Bachelor’s degree in IT or business major from a reputable universityAt least 5 years of senior managerial experienceStrong knowledge in technology and the digital space; will be an advantage if has deep exposure in Online & E-commerce, marketing experience is a strong plusStrong drive for continuous improvement – maximizing growth, accelerating the rate of new customer acquisition and improving program profitabilityDemonstrate a an entrepreneurial attitudeAn analytical, problem solving and results-driven approach to e-commerce challenges and opportunitiesAbility to work well under pressure and balance multiple prioritiesCombination of technical, infrastructure, and most importantly business minded to improve the companyMust be willing to work in a fast-paced environment with an openness to change as our company grows.Strong communication and negotiation skillsEffective management of programs and/or services within area assignedAbility to understand the needs of customersStrong written and presentation skillsGood leadership skillsEnthusiasm for the business you work inProciency in English will be an advantage All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to banking@monroeconsulting.com
